    pass

# To update programmatically without emitting signals:
my_slider_spin.set_value_no_signal(1.5)
```

## Exported Properties

| Property | Type | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `min_value` | float | 0.0 | Minimum value for slider and spinbox |
| `max_value` | float | 1.0 | Maximum value for slider and spinbox |
| `step` | float | 0.01 | Step increment |
| `value` | float | 0.0 | Current value |
| `exp_edit` | bool | false | Exponential slider curve |
| `allow_greater` | bool | false | SpinBox accepts values above max_value |
| `allow_lesser` | bool | false | SpinBox accepts values below min_value |

## Do Not

- Manually create separate HSlider + SpinBox nodes and wire sync logic
- Forget `set_value_no_signal()` when setting values programmatically
